      "writtenOn": "2020-12-23T19:35:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is the idea to value-initialize them? (We would also need to value-initialize fLastControlPointsX and fLastControlPointsY if it\u0027s a round join.)\n\nI would rather not always initialize 40 floats * 2 queues, 32 floats * 1 queue, and 24 floats * 1 queue (544 bytes) every time we process a path. Especially since a lot of paths might not even use each queue, and as long as a queue gets filled up to 4 at least once, that queue doesn\u0027t need to be zero initialized anymore. I prefer the current method of only zero-initializing what\u0027s needed during the final flush.",
